-- Rift Valley Railways' Ondego Relinquishes Chairman Post to Remain as CEO
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2010-11-08T06:02:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/rift-valley-railways-ondego-relinquishes-chairman-post-to-remain-as-ceo.html
Rift Valley Railways Ltd.’s Brown
Ondego said he will relinquish his position as chairman of the
company, which manages the Kenya-Uganda rail line, from January
to retain his post as chief executive officer.  “I have accepted to stay on as CEO so now the board will
have to appoint a chairman,” Ondego said in an interview in
Nairobi today. Ondego, a former managing director of the state-
run Kenya Ports Authority, has held both posts since August,
2008.  To contact the reporter on this story:
